comment_text:
If you watch the movie inception, while trying to get over someone. This track at the end of the movie is gonne hit harder than any drama you've ever seen. There's not many movies that make me tear up, but this one.....the final track and footage bring you from rockbottom to peek happiness in 5 minutes, its just too much.

As much as i love the sounds in this remix. Especially 1:16 and 1:38. And love how you replicated the intensity slowly building up and dropping down like the original. 
Trying to replicate hans emotion in time in a genre dominated by beats is just downright impossible.
That said i think you came closer than everyone who tried before you. The emotion was there and this is truely an amazing track.

Hey Alan, just sending this comment to tell how much your songs made me think about me and how i'm making my life go,

When everyone is childs, they just say to their mom "Sing me to sleep".
Every nights, i'm just Tired.
But to avoid to avoid the fact that i'm tired, i just PLAY.

comment_text: Now that's what I call a real revolution of the Walker Universe! ❤❤❤🎶🎶🖤 Time is also my favorite song by Hans Zimmer.🤣😊.But I should also probably thank you, Alan, for giving the fact that you're the reason I made the best EDM Project in 8th grade last year. Your songs inspired me quite a lot over the years but faded and heading home-like, I was like no he didn't just create a real-life World OF Walker and traveled all over the world to make it's revolution true. Like seeing all the different places you and your team traveled to, just tell everyone that's how much you love your career as a DJ and a musician. And I couldn't be happier from all the work you've been doing, up until now. And not just for your self, but also the distance you've gone to make all your fans happy, and even if you'd had your downs. Still, the fact that I and many other people and walkers and other musicians can look up to you and say "I wanna be Alan Walker when I grow up'' that really just amazes me, because, before any of this, you were just like every other typical DJ, making music in their room. And if it weren't for those people out there to search like crazy for your work, you would've still been in that room creating music. Therefore I'm actually happy you posted your songs online, even if you thought some of them weren't fully perfect.CAuse really no matter how many songs you've done in the past and now, all your walker fans love it. Because you are not just giving them a right to be who they want to be, but to also make them stand up and be that someone. And I just still can't believe how far you've made it, it's crazy insane but also amazing. Like I've seen many DJ'S before, but you started from search to creating your own evolution and your own story, and well I just wanted you to know that after all this LONG text, at the end of the day...I'll always be your number one fan, and no matter what happens, how much hate goes on from non-walkers.I'll always love and support you, because what you've done to support us and make us feel like a walker family isn't big enough to say thank you. You know I was in love with Avicii's music too, and when I heard he died. That hit me hard, cause I really looked up to him in so many ways, and I lost hope for a while and fell into a major sadness and storm of thoughts. And when I came across your music, your live videos here and on Instagram, some of my hope was restored and the fact that many DJ'S made a tribute to him, that healed me even more. Your music helped me get back up and look at a life a totally different way, and I'm just really thankful your still around and you still will be when this coronavirus finally vanishes once in for all, wish you the best of luck and I can't wait to hear more from you.\n~Indira Lechiguero\nAnd to all those people who read through the comments, pls don't be mean to me or Alan, cause I'm not trying to get his attention at all, I just wanna take a moment to appreciate all his work and thank him for inspiring me as any other fan would. Writing a lot is just a thing I tend to do.

comment_text: For me, the composition "Time"  is something more than music. This is something insanely touching, warm and emotional. Each listening plunges you into the past again, again making you feel those emotions. The very ones that you would seem you already forgot, not even dreaming to try them again. But there is one thing that is not subject to space and time — the music of Hans Zimmer. She seemed to open a sealed portal at a time that can no longer be returned. Now I am 31 years old, I live in Russia, I have far from the easiest life, I write through a translator. Sometimes I just don’t understand what to do next, I just can’t force myself to do the impossible. \nBut This music ... since the release of "Inception" motivates me, makes me do the impossible and again restore my will to life. Alan, thank you for distributing this music. Thank you so much. The remix is ​​certainly not as dramatic and powerful as the original, but thanks a lot anyway. If you read this, reader, then please check out the work of Hans Zimmer, one of the greatest composers in history.

comment_text:
Ходунки! Я очень рад поделиться этим видео с вами. Сотрудничество с Хансом Циммером над этим выпуском было совершенно незаурядным опытом на совершенно другом уровне. Каждый, кто знает меня, знает, что я большой поклонник его работы, и это сыграло большую роль в моем музыкальном путешествии. Особенно «Время», которое, наверное, моя любимая песня. Кроме того, в этом году исполняется 10 лет со дня основания. Я очень благодарен за эту возможность!

Создание этого музыкального клипа в мире, находящемся в режиме блокировки, поставило перед нами некоторые очевидные проблемы. Однако мы решили использовать это в своих интересах, и я очень надеюсь, что вам понравится результат. Дайте мне знать, что вы думаете в разделе комментариев ниже!

- Аlan Walker

She said that I need to use my force and change my routine. Lily claimed that we live fast because life is short and time goes fast. She asked me "are you lonely", I said yes and replied that I feel sad sometimes. "This is me" I said to myself, I'm on my way and heading home. I said to her that "I do it all for you" even if I was tired and didn't want to go. My diamond heart showed me a number "135", I called the number and they said to me that "even if everything falls down and even if you're alone, you can reach your goal".
